race.comment: BEYOND MY KEN (1) picked up nicely but was beaten in a tight go first-up over 1000m at Taree. Has never raced over this trip but with a cracking tempo almost certain he can get a nice trail and finish over the top. SIGNATORIES (5) is the danger first-up after a five-month spell. Led all the way to win a Class 1 over this course and distance last June. Should run a big race while fresh despite the terrible gate. MR TRACKSIDE (4) comes here off a seven-week let-up. Has only won twice, both times at today's journey. Comes right into calculations. SUPER FREDS (3) was poor at Kempsey last start but has been freshened up and will find this far easier. LILY BOBTAIL (10) disappointed at Taree last start but the form was rock solid prior to that. Loves racing here so is worth another chance.
